{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "iGOT Deterministic Chatbot — iGOT Karmayogi Support API",
    "description": "REST API for the iGOT Deterministic Chatbot.\n\n## Auth\n\n**Local dev (AUTH_DISABLED=true):** Pass any UUID as `x-authenticated-user-token`. Set `auth_token` collection variable.\n\n**Production:** Pass a real Keycloak JWT as `x-authenticated-user-token`.\n\n## Setup\n\n1. Set `base_url` collection variable (default: `http://localhost:8000`).\n2. Run **Start Session** first — the test script auto-populates `session_id`.\n3. Use `session_id` in all subsequent requests.\n\n## Endpoint order\n1. Health check\n2. Start session → get session_id\n3. GET /sessions/mine → check for active session  \n4. GET /sessions/{id} → restore session\n5. Topic selection (select_choice)\n6. User actions (turn requests)\n7. Admin endpoints",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "session_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-filled by the Start Session test script. Run a Start Session request before using turn endpoints."
    },
    {
      "key": "auth_token",
      "value": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "When AUTH_DISABLED=true in .env, this UUID is used directly as user_id. For production, replace with a real Keycloak JWT."
    },
    {
      "key": "last_session_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Backup copy of the most recently created session_id."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0 — Health",
      "description": "Liveness check — no authentication required.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "id": "f1a2b3c4-d5e6-7890-1234-abcdef012345",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Simple liveness probe. Returns HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\"}` when the server is up. No authentication header needed."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1 — Auth modes (READ FIRST)",
      "description": "These two requests both call POST /ai-chatbot/v1/sessions but demonstrate the two authentication modes. Run one of them first — the test script auto-populates the session_id collection variable.\n\n- WITHOUT JWT: AUTH_DISABLED=true in .env — UUID in auth_token is used directly as user_id.\n- WITH JWT: AUTH_DISABLED=false in .env — pass a real Keycloak JWT.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Session Start — WITHOUT JWT (AUTH_DISABLED=true)",
          "id": "a1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-authenticated-user-token",
                "value": "{{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text",
                "description": "When AUTH_DISABLED=true, this UUID is used directly as user_id. No Keycloak required."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"channel\": \"web\",\n  \"language\": \"en\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ai-chatbot/v1/sessions",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ai-chatbot", "v1", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new chat session using dev/stub auth mode.\n\n**Pre-requisite:** set `AUTH_DISABLED=true` in your `.env` file.\n\nThe UUID in the `auth_token` collection variable is passed as the `x-authenticated-user-token` header. When AUTH_DISABLED=true, this value is used directly as user_id — no Keycloak JWT validation occurs.\n\nThe test script below auto-extracts `session_id` from the response and saves it to the `session_id` collection variable. All subsequent turn requests will use this value via `{{session_id}}`."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const r = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (r.session_id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('session_id', r.session_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('last_session_id', r.session_id);",
                  "    console.log('session_id set to:', r.session_id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('session_id present', () => pm.expect(r.session_id).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Session Start — WITH JWT (AUTH_DISABLED=false)",
          "id": "b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "x-authenticated-user-token",
                "value": "<paste-real-keycloak-jwt-here>",
                "type": "text",
                "description": "Replace this with a real Keycloak JWT obtained from the iGOT portal."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"channel\": \"web\",\n  \"language\": \"en\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/ai-chatbot/v1/sessions",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["ai-chatbot", "v1", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new chat session using a real Keycloak JWT.\n\n**Pre-requisite:** set `AUTH_DISABLED=false` in your `.env` file (or leave it unset — false is the default).\n\nReplace the `x-authenticated-user-token` header value with a real Keycloak JWT from the iGOT portal. The `sub` claim (`f:<x>:<uuid>`) is automatically extracted as `user_id`.\n\nThe test script auto-extracts `session_id` from the response."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const r = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (r.session_id) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('session_id', r.session_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('last_session_id', r.session_id);",
                  "    console.log('session_id set to:', r.session_id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('session_id present', () => pm.expect(r.session_id).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
